parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is on
the airbag may not deploy in the event of a crash
the airbag may deploy randomly while driving
the passenger airbag is disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights do not illuminate
daytime running lights do not illuminate
smoke comes from the instrument control panel
warning light illuminated on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair under recall can lead to continued safety risks, as the original issue may not be fully addressed, and may also cause frustration and inconvenience for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Issues persist after recall repair
dealerships are unresponsive or uncooperative
manufacturers deny assistance with repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates while shifting gears
the transmission slips or fails to engage properly
the check engine light comes on
the transmission warning light comes on
the vehicle has difficulty maintaining a steady speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag warning light to come on, indicating a potential safety risk, and may prevent the airbag from deploying in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
the passenger airbag sensor indicates "off" or "not working"
the airbag warning light flashes or comes on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine light coming on and going off intermittently can indicate a range of potential issues, including faulty sensors, ignition problems, or engine misfires, which can lead to decreased performance, fuel efficiency, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The engine light comes on and goes off intermittently
the engine light stays on constantly
the vehicle experiences decreased performance or fuel efficiency
the vehicle has difficulty starting or running.
